cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.PL

The paper deals with AI synthesis problems and specifically with constraint satisfaction problems. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of possibility distributions, which is a topic related to machine learning and probability theory, making cs.LG a likely category as well. The implementation of classical techniques such as Backtracking and Forward Checking suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories cs.DS and cs.SE, which deal with data structures and software engineering, respectively. Finally, the paper discusses the formalization of a new type of constraint satisfaction problem, which could be related to the category cs.PL, which deals with programming languages and formal methods.
